{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Cm5hSJrVC9qBHpvVCnoTUU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sprint 1 complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## What was built\n\n**`src/lib/identity.ts`** — the core identity resolution module with:\n- `validateEvent` — runtime validation with TypeScript `asserts` narrowing\n- `resolveIdentityMapping` — checks `identity_mappings FINAL`, inserts new mappings, no-ops on same user, throws `IdentityConflictError` (status 409) on conflict\n- `insertEvent` — validates, timestamps, inserts to `events`, calls mapping logic when both IDs are present, returns `EventRow` with `resolved_id`\n- `queryEventsWithResolvedId` — LEFT JOIN `events` + `identity_mappings FINAL` with `coalesce` for retroactive identity resolution; optional filters for event_name, resolved_id, before-cursor, limit\n- `getEventsByResolvedId` — convenience wrapper\n\n**Key design choice:** all functions accept an optional `client` parameter (default: singleton) so integration tests can inject a `minipanel_test`-scoped client without env-var tricks.\n\n## Self-evaluation results\n\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| `pnpm test` | 33 passing, 16 skipped (integration suite — no live ClickHouse in this env) |\n| `pnpm lint` | 22 files, no issues |\n| `pnpm typecheck` | exit 0 |\n| `pnpm build` | exit 0 |"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":299,"cache_read_input_tokens":74180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":299},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"656b7ba5-00e6-4c89-8031-4b9e0c97ac54","uuid":"9445dae5-4f67-4e9e-aef8-9844a19c1473"}
